annotation.TEXT: Demo count: 9

...I just checked how much total video footage I had during that little pause there, and it's less than 5 minutes so far, so I'll play one more level now! (Huh, it sure seemed like I had played longer than that...)
Yeah, it's 4-1, so... Lakitu. Can I kill him with the back of my head?
Space-time rewind count: 6
Now, let's not enter that pipe this time...

(On a related note, I think there's a place in The Lost Levels where there's a row of invisible coin blocks in a level containing Hammer Brothers, and they can stand on those invisible coin blocks too.)
Huh. There's a small gap in the overhang here that's not in the original game. That'll easily let me enter a pipe before the "Welcome to warp zone!" message appears, but...
Let's back off a bit here. I don't need to be that close to the right edge of the screen.
Umm... Nope. I'm not entering any of these pipes unless you force me to by stopping the screen scroll!

Alright, I'm back here, so let's just finish the level normally. Now, if the flag is missing for whatever reason, you won't get points for grabbing the flagpole at all, but you can still clear the level, and fireworks still work.
Whoops, I keep doing that. Well, it's not like I needed both flowers right now... Although I can certainly see why there are two power ups here!
Hiyah! Nice!
Oh, this room looks familiar. I'll just grab some coins and an unneeded power up and leave. (Please don't make me emerge in a lousy place!)
Umm... Probably not, and I think I'm stuck now. Why did the hack allow me to jump over that flagpole if there was nothing good behind it?
Yeah, that was definitely a good idea. However...

Okay, that 1-up was a little more challenging to reach, but the real challenge may be hitting that ? block in the wall there. However, I think I could actually get to it, if there weren't flying cheepos around.
Umm... What the heck is that glitchy-looking thing?
Oh, and my regular demo count shall remain at 9, because the first death that started that infinite death loop there was pretty much my fault.
And we have another oddly-placed springboard here, which seems to be totally pointless.
Huh. I'm actually a little surprised that the game didn't hand me a free 1-up from those bricks there.
Yeah, 5000 wasn't happening this time, but at least the fireworks are!
Space-time rewind count: 5
Ooh, the Bowser fire generator appeared, which means no more cheepos! Alright, let's try this and hope I get lucky...
Okay, if I inch the screen over just enough here...
And, Bowser has now felt the power of toasty! Now, let me guess... The axe will result in a fake Kaizo trap again, right?

Sweet! The Bowser fire didn't get in my way and I hit the block! Too bad it was only a coin... (Also, I went back and checked the rest of those bricks later, and none of them contained anything besides the 1-up that I already got here.)
Space-time rewind count: 8
Oh, back for more? Well, this time I can just do a regular stomp easily. Now... Should I take the top route or the bottom route here?
LOL. Wow... Even without considering that hidden block, I don't know what I was thinking there, trying to jump full speed towards a tall wall...
Oh, man. I guess we're going bullet crazy again.
Yeah, I figured that pipe led somewhere.
Uh, oh! Flying cheepos! Also, there's a green one swimming through the ceiling up there for some reason.
And, I did it again. Ooh, but at least I ended up with a star!
...Well, it's both flammable and inflammable, apparently.
What the heck?! Wow, this is lame. That's the worst possible place for midpoint, because I can't even save myself by holding A as I appear, due to that platform being in the way.

Yeah, as I thought. Doing that just resets the room, and doesn't send you to world -1 or anything like that. It works the same way in the original game's 8-7-6 warp zone area (which is indeed possible to do if you know how).
Demo count: Infinity+1
Huh. I was so expecting to be able to enter that pipe, end up in the warp zone area again, and use another space-time rewind.
Demo count: Infinity+2
And, yep. This is indeed the 8-7-6 warp zone. I guess I could show you guys a sneak peek of 8-1 before I space-time rewind back to before I entered this area.

And fortunately, I still advance to the next world normally even though Mario was still in his walking animation there. Now you might remember how I briefly showed the beginning of this level in episode 1 when I entered a warp zone pipe. Well, now I'm here for realsies!
Woo, lucky stomp.
What happened last time was I ended up entering that tiny horizontal pipe next to the koopas down there when I phased through the wall.

Seriously, ACMLM! How could you put the midpoint there? Up 'til now, your levels may have been odd, but they didn't have any design flaws that doomed all of the player's lives like this! ...Obviously, I'm going to use another space-time rewind here.

And, I believe this is the exact same 8-7-6 warp zone area as in the original game, except the mushroom platforms have been replaced with bullet cannons. That'll make getting all of the coins somewhat tricky.
Aha! Just as planned!

Yeah, this appears to be another Hammer Brother themed level, but this time my goal is to fry them instead of star-kill them. Interestingly, they can stand on rows of coins... and can end up getting themselves stuck on the roof as well. Oops.
AHH!!! Flying cheepos! Get me outta here!
I'm expecting Lakitu to show up again at any time now... maybe.
DOUBLE KILL!
Whoa, this is dangerous. Also, dead-ends mean nothing to me when I'm on a moving platform! ...What the?!
Wow, I even phased through the base of the flagpole, but I'm not gonna keep going to the right, because it's probably just an infinite road to nowhere, like usual.
Umm... Yeah, that was weird. Okay, let's take the upper route here this time and not enter any more pipes for the rest of the level!
Alright, I've decided to go back to this point, where I'll try taking the lower path this time.
Entering that pipe apparently wasn't, as I'm back here again. One moment, please...
And there's yet another gimme 1-up. This hack sure likes to hand them out like candy!
Okay, there he is. It took him longer than I expected, and I'm practically at the goal now.
Well, I chose the top, and it looks like I missed out on a pipe on the bottom. Oh, well.
Oh, good. Looks like this pipe exit is set properly. And I bet that wall behind me is what I could have crossed using that hidden block that "helped" me fall to my death earlier.
Nuts. I jumped too late, and I knew it as I hit the jump button there.
Space-time rewind count: 4
I'm guessing this pipe would send me to world 5, even though the "Welcome to warp zone!" message didn't appear, but of course, I'm skipping that one too.

Surprisingly, no. I got shoved through a brick wall and up against the base of a flagpole (which I could've reached by going on the ceiling at the start), but there was no pit for me to automatically walk into this time.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! ...Un momento, por favor...
Space-time rewind count: 7
Umm... No level clear music? That's strange... I don't know what caused that to not play.
Whoa, look at all those down elevators. I'm just gonna go over the top here. Be careful, as they can pull you down through solid ledges if you let them.
Well, I guess that's it for this level. Huh. The flag's missing. Also, I think I can jump over the flagpole. Anything good hidden behind it?
It seems like there might be something hidden in that upper row of bricks there, but I don't feel like making risky jumps to check right now. (I checked later, and they didn't contain anything.)
Well, I'm not going to wait for time to expire here...
Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros., where I'll start off by collecting some coins!

Alright, that'll do it for this episode... for realsies this time! Join me next time, when I'll finish world 4 and probably start world 5! And now I leave you with a sneak peek of world 4-3! To be continued...
Hey there, Toads. How's it going? Let me guess... My princess is in another castle, right?
Man, could you imagine trying to do this level without fireballs?
Ah, that's better. Alright, let's keep going to the right. I think jumping on top of that midair triple-decker cannon would be a good idea.
Alright, that'll do it for this episode. Next time, I'll take on the rest of world 4! ...Or, actually...
Okay, this castle begins with yet another oddly-placed springboard, which I guess could be used to get onto the roof to the right, but as usual, I'm staying down here.
